The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai/Johannesburg, July 24: Bharti Airtel and South Africas MTN are expected to extend exclusive talks by at least two to three weeks for a proposed merger, sources said on Friday. The two firms in May agreed to hold exclusive talks till July 31 but may now extend it, given the complexity of the deal.                            
	 New Delhi, July 24: IRDA has asked general insurance companies to review underwriting practices of products that they have been selling for over two years. Chairman J. Hari Narayan said marine, fire and motor insurance policies should be reviewed.                             
	 New Delhi, July 24: The Supreme Court will on Monday hear a petition by Harsh Lodha seeking a stay on the Company Law Board interim order that bars him from chairing the annual general meeting of Birla Corporation on that day.                            
	 Mumbai, July 24: Sebi said regulations that prohibit employees from selling their firms shares bought in the past six months, or vice versa, do not apply to Esops.                                                                                                                           
